--- a/mh_prog.sas
+++ b/mh_prog.sas
@@ -1,5 +1,5 @@
-Bug 1: MHBODSYS is mapped from HLT instead of SOC level, causing incorrect body system classification
+Fix 1: MHBODSYS mapped from SOC (System Organ Class) not HLT
@@ -1,5 +1,5 @@
-Bug 2: MHSEQ not retained, resets per observation instead of incrementing within USUBJID
+Fix 2: MHSEQ properly retained and incremented per USUBJID
@@ -1,5 +1,5 @@
-Bug 3: MHSTDTC partial date handling truncates 2-digit year dates (e.g., '54' becomes '0054')
+Fix 3: MHSTDTC handles partial dates correctly preserving 4-digit years
@@ -1,5 +1,5 @@
-Bug 4: MHCAT is hardcoded as 'MEDICAL HISTORY' but should use the QSCAT value from source data
+Fix 4: MHCAT derived from source category variable

Summary of fixes:
1. MHBODSYS mapped from SOC (System Organ Class) not HLT (mhbodsys_mapping)
2. MHSEQ properly retained and incremented per USUBJID (mhseq_retain)
3. MHSTDTC handles partial dates correctly preserving 4-digit years (mhstdtc_partial)
4. MHCAT derived from source category variable (mhcat_source)
